2003 Grand Nationals Entry Form
NASA Grand Nationals
Powerlifting, Power Sports & BP Only Championships
Date: Saturday, and Sunday, 2003
Location: Ramada Hickory, 1607 Fairgrove Church Rd., Conover, NC. 828-465-1100
Meet Director: Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068 405-527-8513 sqbpdl@aol.com
Official Weigh-In Times- PL'ing, BP Only & Power Sports
Early Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 pm, Friday (All Women and Men 119-205)
Regular Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 am, Saturday (All Women and Men 119-205)
Early Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 pm, Saturday (Men 227-SHW)
Regular Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 am, Sunday (Men 227-SHW)
Lifting will begin at 10:00 am both days.

Rules: All Current NASA Rules will apply. View the entire NASA Rule Book on our Web Site at www.nasa-sports.com. All lifters are required to have a current NASA Membership Card. Cards will be available at the meet or can be ordered from our web site. Membership Cards are good for 1 full year from the date of their purchase. Adult Membership is $25.00 per year and Senior Lifters (65+ years of age) & High School Memberships are $15.00 per year. All lifters MUST wear a Wrestling Suit or other one piece suit. NO CANVAS SUITS OR SHIRTS ARE ALLOWED.

Divisions for Powerlifting & Bench Press Only (equipment allowed) and Power Sports
Pure: Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Natural: Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Novice: Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free, never one first in any NASA National Meet.
Teenage: 13-19 years of age, Anabolic steroid Free for minimum of 3 years.
High School: Currently HS enrolled lifters, Anabolic Steroid Free for life.
Junior: 13-23 years of age, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Intermediate: 24-29 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for 3 years minimum.
Sub-Master-1: 30-34 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Sub-Master-2: 35-39 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Sub-Masters Pure: 30-39 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for Life.
Masters-1: 40-49 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-2: 50-59 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-3: 60-69 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-4: 70+ years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-5: 40+ years of age, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free lifters only.
Power Sports (raw) Championships Entry Info

Rules: All Current NASA Rules will apply. No Supportive Equipment of any kind is allowed in Power Sports Divisions Only. Lifts included in Power Sports are Strict Curl, Bench Press & Deadlift for Total (Full Meet), or you may enter any Individual Lift. Squat is a Single Lift Meet Only in Power Sports. View the entire NASA Rule Book on our Web Site at www.nasa-sports.com. All lifters are required to have a current NASA Membership Card. Cards will be available at the meet or can be ordered from our web site. Membership Cards are good for 1 full year from the date of their purchase. Adult Membership is $25.00 per year and Senior Lifters (65+ years of age) and High School Memberships are $15.00 per year. All lifters MUST wear a Wrestling Suit or other one piece suit.
Men’s Weight Classes
Women’s Weight Class
Power Sports Entry Fee’s Only
“Power Sports Full Meet (Curl, BP & DL) = $45.00
Strict Curl Only= $40.00, Squat Only= $40.00, Bench Only=$40.00, Deadlift Only= $40.00
Combination of Any Two Single Lift Events= $70.00
Any 3 Individual Single Lift Events=$90.00     Any 3 Individual Events & Full Meet = $129.95

Awards: 1st thru 5th Place Awards for each weight class in each Division for Powerlifting, BP Only and Power Sports Contests. Awards will consist of (New-Special Awards will be offered this year also) Column Trophies, Large Plaques and Medium Plaques.
Return Entry and Entry Fee’s
Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068
Or you may Enter On-Line from our web site at www.nasa-sports.com
Entry Fee’s

Powerlifting and Bench Press Only (Equipted) : $45.00 for first division entered, $35.00 for each additional entry. Late Fee after Deadline Date is $5.00 additional fee, per division entered. Cash Only for all late entries.
Power Sports Entry Fee’s are posted on the Power Sports portion of this entry form.
Team Entry Fee

$30.00 per Team Entry. This fee is for the Team Trophy. Team Rosters MUST be turned in by the start of lifting on Saturday. Trophies for 1st thru 3rd for Powerlifting, BP Only and Power Sports Teams. Maximum of 10 members per team.
